cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper deals with hyperspectral target detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves learning target signatures using a multiple instance learning framework, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The approach also involves maximizing the response of a hybrid sub-pixel detector, which involves optimization and potentially deep learning techniques (cs.AI). The paper also involves experiments with simulated and real hyperspectral data, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
